":"regiment8-14","name":"4th Fleet","legend":"Regiment was formed in 717 Gaveham Era during the Witian Campaign. 4th Fleet is based in Frample. \r\n\r\nRegiment composition in 723 GE:\r\n— fleet: 1."},{"id":"regiment8-15","name":"5th Fleet","legend":"Regiment was formed in 721 Gaveham Era during the Seabingian War. 5th Fleet is based in Botherston. \r\n\r\nRegiment composition in 723 GE:\r\n— fleet: 1."},{"id":"burg29","name":"Holoquay","legend":"<p><em>HOLO-QUE-WAY</em></p>"},{"id":"burg38","name":"Kiyomura","legend":"<p><em>(KIO-MURA)</em></p>\n<p>A busy port city of Niveara, handles most of the trade for Niveara's northern shipping lanes.</p>"},{"id":"label1","name":"Aeropeligo Pass","legend":"<p>The only land route to Aeropeligo Island</p>"},{"id":"stateLabel2","name":"Grand Republic of Kiberia","legend":"<p><em>(KAI-BEER-EE-AH)</em></p>"},{"id":"stateLabel5","name":"Korathis","legend":"<p><em>(CORE-RAH-THIS)</em></p>"},{"id":"stateLabel8","name":"Federal Republic of Felisara","legend":"<p><em>(FELLA-SARA)</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Closed off, beefs hard with Korathis</li>\n<li>Is okay with other countries</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ellsworth the Capital of Felisara<br><br></p>"},{"id":"stateLabel6","name":"United Provinces of Lyronda","legend":""},{"id":"stateLabel7","name":"The Morenthos Empire","legend":"<p><em>(MORE-EN-TOES)</em></p>"},{"id":"label3","name":"Stansted Canal","legend":"<p>A man made canal linking the northern and southern ocean allowing the connection of sea routes between the two</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":"marker0","name":"Crimson Syndicate Controlled Port","legend":"<p>The Dockyard that Cade works at, connected to the Ironport.</p>"},{"id":"label5","name":"The Pildon Strait","legend":"<p>Because the Federal Republic of Felisara controls the Pildon Strait, Korathis relies heavily on Kiberia for imports and trade as they have a bad standing with Felisara.</p>"},{"id":"label7","name":"Unanamed forest","legend":"<p>Forest Boreal Native shit</p>"},{"id":"burg23","name":"Neravos","legend":"<p>The northern most port city of Felisara.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":"river7","name":"The Corvoy River","legend":"<p>The main river used for carrying goods up through Dubea and into the foothills of the Sentinel Mountains of Vinova.</p>"},{"id":"burg48","name":"Lynden","legend":"<p>Capital the state of Dubrea</p>\n<p>The main port city of the northern trade sea routes of Felisara, located closely to many foreign trade hubs and more importantly the Cairenport Canal, Lynden is perfectly placed to take advantage of the rich trade passing through the area.&nbsp;</p>"}]
